Put a Caller on Hold Using the Softphone

Salesforce CRM Call Center lets you put any caller on hold.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials to Developer Editions

To put a caller on hold: click Hold on the active softphone line. The Hold Time clock starts, and the line light icon blinks yellow.

Callers are automatically put on hold when initiating a call transfer, dialing a second number, or starting a conference call.

To resume the call, click Retrieve from Hold. To end the call without retrieving the caller, click End Call.

Some features may be unavailable due to customizations for your organization. See your administrator for details.

Get to Know Your Softphone Features
title: How to Put a Caller on Hold Using Salesforce CRM Call Center
